Bookshelf: A Bookshelf is a piece of furniture that is used to store books. It can be made of wood, metal, or plastic and typically has shelves that are adjustable to accommodate books of different sizes. Bookshelves can be placed in a room or a library and can be arranged in a variety of ways to create a visually appealing display of books.
